node.text:
We are obsessed with these excellent quality, glassy and naturally etched Spodumene crystals from Afghanistan.💙💗💚💛 Pure Spodumene is a colorless lithium aluminum silicate and varieties of colored Spodumene are due to trace elements of Manganese and Iron within giving it a range of tones from pink, yellow, green, purple and rarely blue.

Most people recognize this mineral as “Kunzite”, although technically Kunzite is the name for the pink variety of Spodumene and “Hiddenite” is the name given to the yellow/green variety.

Spodumene crystals are tenebrescent meaning they are extremely sensitive to changing conditions like sunlight (UV), heat and radiation which can alter their color drastically, so it is very important that they are kept inside and out of the sun. The color and degree in which it will change to depends heavily on its trace elements within the Spodumene.

Blue variety Spodumene is so rare because they are only blue right when they emerge from the ground and can quickly change color and clarity when exposed to sunlight or heat. We keep our blue Spodumene crystals in a box in a drawer to prevent any change from happening.

As stated by the Gemological Institute of America, “Kunzite is pleochroic, which means it can display different colors in different crystal directions. Kunzite displays its best, most intense color down the length of its crystals.” Spodumene is associated with reaching deep meditative states to releases stress and anxiety. Additionally pink and purple Kunzite is associated with unconditional love, an open heart and compassion. Green and yellow Hiddenite is associated with personal and spiritual growth, new beginnings and a connection to the earth.

We hope you enjoyed this beautiful compilation of high grade Spodumene crystals and learned a bit about them too!🙏💎❤️ Information Source: Status Report On Gemstones From Afghanistan, by Gary W. Bowersox. Originally published in  GEMS & GEMOLOGY, Winter, 1985 🎶Music: @Squeedabeats - Safe from Myself

Here at Rocks for the Spirit we are totally obsessed with Rutilated Quartz. Rutile inclusions display a beautiful and mesmerizing shimmer of light. In this video we feature some of our recent favorite, high quality Rutilated Quartz crystals including Silver, Red, and Gold colored Rutile. The crystals featured in this video are for your viewing pleasure and they are not for sale. Rutile is a metallic mineral that typically grows in thin needles inside of Quartz crystals. All of the crystals in this video are polished or shaped to highlight the amazing Rutile inclusions inside.

Interesting facts about Rutile:
Rutile crystals have the special optical properties of high refractive index and high dispersion which creates beautiful rainbows and a mesmerizing play of light.

The word Rutile is derived from the Latin word Rutilus which means red.

Asterisms found in star Ruby, star Sapphire, and star Rose Quartz are caused by micro inclusions of fibrous Rutile.

Rutile is primarily composed of titanium dioxide and it sometimes forms aligned in a perfect six rayed star.

node.text:
We put together a compilation of some of our favorite Tourmaline crystals for you all to enjoy. A wide variety of Tourmaline colors are shown in this video including, Black, Green, Blue, and Pink. Some have high translucency while others are opaque but all of them have a completely natural form and have not been polished or cut. It is mesmerizing to watch light reflect off the beautiful striations (vertical growth lines) and terminations (natural ending of the crystals).

node.text: On our recent trip to Big Sur, California, there was only one evening where it was clear enough to enjoy the majestic beauty of the Sunset over the vast Pacific Ocean. We were in the middle of cooking dinner in our camper van and realized the sun was setting so we ran down to the cliffs at the beachside with this Black Tourmalinated Quartz freeform. When we held it up to the sunset we noticed the interesting optical effect it had in beautifully distorting the image in front of our faces! We just wanted to share this lovely experience we had with you all and wish you a wonderful weekend😌🙏❤️🌊✨

Take a tour with us of some of the most incredible crystals on earth! Since you loved the last giant crystal video we posted so much, we searched through our large video collection and selected some of our favorites to share with you from the Denver and Tucson gem shows💕We will be back with our vendors shortly so feel free to send us a message with serious inquiries🙌
.
As promised, we will be announcing the Opal giveaway winner from last week's IGTV video in just a couple hours at noon PST in our story, so be sure to check out that post to get your last second entries in! . 
We would love to know your favorite part of this video in the comments below and also what kind of video you'd like to see from us next 😉 We hope you enjoyed all of the giant crystal magic and stay tuned for more coming soon!💎❤️💫
.
Music: Lakey Inspired

🔮Which of these five 💎's are you most excited for in tomorrow's update?🥳
🌈1-Rainbow Obsidian 
🌵2-Laguna Agates 
🌸3-Neon Pink Labradorite 
☀️4-Sunstone/Moonstone sphere🌙
🌿5-Green Tourmaline crystals
.
If you missed the announcement, we are updating our site tomorrow at 5 pm PST with over 160 brand new crystals and trust us, you're not gonna want to miss this one 😜 Hope you're all having a beautiful week so far and we hope you'll stop by tomorrow!!❤️💜
